Package: pprof
Type: Package
Title: Risk-adjusted Models, Standardized Measure Calculation, Hypothesis Testing and Visualization for Provider Profiling
Version: 1.3
Date: 2024-11-12
Authors@R: c(
   person("Yubo", "Shao", email = "ybshao@umich.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
   person("Wenbo", "Wu", email = "Wenbo.Wu@nyulangone.org", role = "aut"),
   person("Kevin", "He", email = "kevinhe@umich.edu", role = "aut"),
   person("Tao", "Xu", email = "taoxu@med.umich.edu", role = c("ctb")))
Description: Implements linear and generalized linear models for provider profiling,
    incorporating both fixed and random effects. For large-scale providers, the linear 
    profiled-based method and the SerBIN method (Wu et al., 2022) for binary data 
    reduce the computational burden. Provides post-modeling features including 
    indirect and direct standardization measures, hypothesis testing, 
    confidence intervals, and post-estimation visualization.
